  "text": "It has been shown in [CITATION_1] , the total number of obstacles N between two nodes separated by distance r 0 is a Poisson random variable with mean βr 0 + p. The probability that there exist a LOS link between Alice and Eve with distance r 0 , i.e there are no obstacles between them is P (LOS Eve ) = P (N = 0) = e −(βr0+p) .",
